    "## 1.1 Why Machine Learning?\n",
    "\n",
    "Machine learning is about **extracting knowledge from data**. It sits at the intersection of statistics, artificial intelligence, and computer science.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Traditional Rule-Based Approach vs Machine Learning\n",
    "\n",
    "| Approach | Description | Limitation |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **Handcoded Rules** | `if/else` logic designed by experts | Brittle, hard to scale, domain-specific |\n",
    "| **Machine Learning** | Learns patterns from examples automatically | Requires data; less interpretable |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Example:** A spam filter can be built with keyword blacklists — but this breaks whenever spammers change their wording. An ML spam filter *learns* patterns automatically from thousands of labeled emails.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🎯 When is Machine Learning the Right Tool?\n",
    "- When a problem is **too complex** for handcoded rules\n",
    "- When the solution **needs to adapt** over time\n",
    "- When you have **lots of data** and need insight"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8b37b1fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.2 Types of Machine Learning Problems\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔵 Supervised Learning\n",
    "The algorithm learns from **labeled examples** (input-output pairs).\n",
    "- **Classification**: Predict a *category* (e.g., is this email spam or not?)\n",
    "- **Regression**: Predict a *continuous value* (e.g., what will the house price be?)\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🟢 Unsupervised Learning\n",
    "No labels are provided — the algorithm finds **structure in the data itself**.\n",
    "- **Clustering**: Group similar customers together\n",
    "- **Dimensionality Reduction**: Compress data while preserving information\n",
    "- **Anomaly Detection**: Find unusual patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🟡 Reinforcement Learning\n",
    "An agent learns by **interacting with an environment** and receiving rewards or penalties (e.g., training a robot to walk).\n",
    "\n",
    "> 📘 **This book focuses primarily on Supervised and Unsupervised Learning.**"
   ]
  },
