    "## 1.5 Training and Test Split\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theory: Why Split the Data?\n",
    "\n",
    "We cannot use the same data to both **train** and **evaluate** a model — if we do, the model could simply memorize the training data (overfitting) and appear to perform perfectly while failing on new data.\n",
    "\n",
    "The solution is to split the data:\n",
    "- **Training set (~75%)**: Used to teach the model\n",
    "- **Test set (~25%)**: Used to evaluate how well the model generalizes to *new, unseen* data\n",
    "\n",
    "This mimics the real-world scenario where your model sees new data it was never trained on."
   ]
  },
