    "## 1.7 Building the First Model: k-Nearest Neighbors\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theory: How Does k-NN Work?\n",
    "\n",
    "k-Nearest Neighbors (k-NN) is one of the simplest ML algorithms:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Store all training examples\n",
    "2. For a new data point, find the **k closest** training examples (neighbors)\n",
    "3. The prediction = **majority vote** among those k neighbors\n",
    "\n",
    "**Distance metric:** By default, Euclidean distance — the straight-line distance in feature space.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$d(x, y) = \\sqrt{\\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - y_i)^2}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key parameter:** `k` — with `k=1`, the model memorizes training data perfectly but may not generalize well. Larger `k` gives smoother, more general decision boundaries.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pros:** Simple, no training phase, naturally handles multi-class  \n",
    "**Cons:** Slow prediction on large datasets, sensitive to irrelevant features"
   ]
  },
